</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/victory-day-2025-rehearsal-honour-guard-st-petersburg.png" alt="Honour guard soldiers march during a rehearsal for the Victory Day military parade, which will take place at Dvortsovaya Square on May 9 to celebrate 80 years since World War II in St. Petersburg" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Honour guard soldiers march during a rehearsal for the Victory Day military parade, which will take place at Dvortsovaya Square on May 9 to celebrate 80 years since World War II in St. Petersburg. Credits: Dmitri Lovetsky/The Associated Press</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Russia declared a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h1-1-72-hour-unilateral-ceasefire" target="_blank">72-hour unilateral ceasefire</a> from May 8 to May 11, which coincided with the 80th anniversary of Victory Day (a Russian holiday that commemorates the victory of the Soviet Union over Nazi Germany), and called on Kyiv to accept the truce. They also warned Ukraine of an ‚Äúadequate and effective‚Äù response in the event of ceasefire violations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Ukraine responded by demanding an immediate month-long ceasefire. President Zelenskyy said the truce shouldn‚Äôt just be for conducting Victory Day parades and urged Russia to provide a basis for real diplomacy. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The White House said Donald Trump wanted ‚Äúa permanent ceasefire.‚Äù US Secretary of State Marco Rubio engaged with his Russian counterpart, Sergey Lavrov, and emphasized the need to end the war. He also said there was scope for optimism and realism in envisioning a ceasefire. 
         </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Meanwhile, French President Emmanuel Macron said Ukraine's western allies will "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h1-2-increase-pressure-on-russia" target="_blank">increase pressure on Russia</a>" over the next 10 days and adopt a firmer line against President Putin. On the other hand, North Korea confirmed for the first time that it has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h1-3-sent-troops-to-fight" target="_blank">sent troops to fight</a> for Russia in the war with Ukraine. 
         </p>
        
        </mj-text>
