        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">The US detachment and ramifications</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-foreign-aid-pause-global-impact-ngos.png" alt="As the United States paused foreign assistance to countries worldwide, confusion, panic, and desperation have gripped many organizations that benefit from the funds" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>As the United States paused foreign assistance to countries worldwide, confusion, panic, and desperation have gripped many organizations that benefit from the funds. Credits: OSV News photo/Nancy McNally, Catholic Relief Services</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          As Trump marks his 100th day in office, some of his administration's decisions are having consequences. Critics say his recent moves, including dismantling USAID, budget cuts, and closing bureaus, could erode Washington's soft power. This move puts the US‚Äôs global leadership and national security at risk and could open the floodgates for adversaries like China and Russia to strengthen their influence, especially in Africa.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Through its Belt and Road Initiative, China has been strongly involved in mines and other resource projects across Africa. China is also seen as a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h2-4-more-favorable-partner" target="_blank">more favorable partner</a>, as it does not interfere in internal affairs, attaches no political conditions, and does not make empty promises.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Russia is trying to expand its influence by providing security assistance, political backing at the UN, and inexpensive weaponry to the region. They have also expanded their military bases in Libya, Sudan, and the Central African Republic. Moreover, the country might also be interested in Africa‚Äôs rare earth minerals. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The US has the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h2-5-african-growth-and-opportunity-act" target="_blank">African Growth and Opportunity Act</a> (AGOA), which is similar to China's Belt and Road Initiative in Africa but not as extensive. Its goal is to assist Sub-Saharan economies while improving US relations with these countries. It expires in September of this year, and many African countries are concerned that it may not be renewed due to current developments.</p>
        </mj-text>
