          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">China tips towards Pakistan</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: China is looking for an independent investigation into the deadly attack in Kashmir, while Pakistan asks for monetary support.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          China is calling for an <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h3-6-impartial-investigation" target="_blank">impartial investigation</a> into the Pahalgam attack that killed 26 people. The Chinese FM Wang Yi assured his Pakistani counterpart Mohammad Ishaq Dar of China‚Äôs backing in Pakistan‚Äôs sovereignty and security. He urged both India and Pakistan to show restraint and prevent escalation.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          India announced many measures against Pakistan, including suspending the Indus Waters Treaty and closing the land border crossing at Attar. In retaliation, Pakistan unveiled countermeasures, such as closing its airspace to Indian airliners and suspending all trade. Dar called India‚Äôs moves baseless propaganda against Pakistan and appreciated China‚Äôs support.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Meanwhile, Indian External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar spoke to his British counterpart, David Lammy, and ‚Äúunderlined the importance of zero tolerance for terrorism.‚Äù The world leaders have condemned the attack and expressed solidarity with India.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          In a separate development, Pakistan asked China for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-h3-7-additional-monetary-support" target="_blank">additional monetary support</a> of $1.4B. This comes after the company used its current $4.3B facility. The plea was made on April 27 during the meetings of the IMF and World Bank in Washington.</p>
        </mj-text>
