          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Jordan Bardella of the French far-right National Rally (RN) party plans to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-04-2025-br2-9-run-for-president" target="_blank">run for president</a> in 2027, if Marine Le Pen is unable to do so due to a judicial issue. Le Pen, who has run for president three times, is appealing a conviction for embezzlement, which bars her from public office for five years.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The 29-year-old, who currently leads the party, is seen as her prot√©g√©. He says that he will step in to run as the candidate for the RN if she isn‚Äôt able to, stressing the importance of unity. Other potential candidates include former PMs √âdouard Philippe and Gabriel Attal and Justice Minister G√©rald Darmanin.</p>
